Organization Name: DEPARTMENT OF PORT SHIPPING AND AVIATION UT OF LAKSHADWEEP
Project Name: Construction of passenger jetty and associated landside facilities on the western side of the Kadmath Island, Lakshadweep.
Alternative Site Examined: Not applicable as the project or activity is site specific
Project Description: Kadmath island is the longest island among the four inhabited islands located in Aminidivi atoll between Amini island in south and Chetlat island in north, Kadmath is the centremost island of Lakshadweep Union Territory. For better and safe Intra-island travel Lakshadweep Administration has engaged Cochin Port Authority (CoPA) as Project Management Consultants for providing technical support / consultancy services for development of Kadmath Island. The proposed facilities are: ;i)	Construction of jetty of dimension 70 m long and 12 m wide ;ii)	Approach trestle connecting to land - 75 m long & width varying from 10 to 18.4 m. ;iii)	Finger jetty- 50 m long and 8.5 m wide;iv)	Boat landing centre- 75 m long and 20 m wide ;v)	3 storeyed passenger facilitation centre with modern amenities of plinth area 500 Sq. m ;vi)	Boat repair shed near boat landing centre of plinth area 150 Sq. m.;vii) Ice plant - 150 Sq.m;viii) Fuel Station 77 Sq. m;ix) Pumphouse -220 Sq. m;x) 2 Nos of external roads;;

Organization Name: SOLAR ENERGY CORPORATION OF INDIA LIMITED
Project Name: Floating Solar PV Power Plant for Lakshadweep Island (Kavaratti)
Alternative Site Examined: Not applicable as the project or activity is site specific
Project Description: The proposed Floating Solar PV project has a capacity of 5 MW (AC) / 6 MWp (DC) and includes essential components such as floats, PV modules, cables, and inverters, all installed on a lagoon. An onshore substation will connect the solar panels via an offshore marine cable, allowing solar power to be transmitted to a 16 MWh Battery Energy Storage System (BESS) or directly to transmission lines for further distribution to the local grid. At the Kavaratti location, the transmission line spans approximately 200 meters.

Project Name: Development of Marine and Land facilities at Androth Island in Lakshadweep
Alternative Site Examined: Not applicable as the project or activity is site specific
Project Description: Lakshadweep Administration has engaged Cochin Port Authority as Project Management Consultants for providing technical support / consultancy services to UTLA in development of Port and Shipping infrastructures and operation in Lakshadweep Islands. The proposed development consists of: ;;•	Refurbishment of the existing 530 m long breakwater;•	Extension of breakwater to an additional length of 490 m to ensure safe entry into harbour;•	Construction of 150 m multipurpose jetty to meet  requirements of Navy;•	Construction of 250 m multipurpose jetty to meet  requirements of UTLA;•	Dredging the basin to (-) 8.1 m CD;•	Berth corner lights and other Navigational aids required for night berthing;•	Development of slipway and ancillary facilities to facilitate fishermen and Navy;•	Development of storage facilities on reclaimed land;•	Redevelop passenger facilitation centre with modern amenities;•	Development of road connectivity;•	Providing utilities services including CCTV with night vision  ;;;

Project Name: Construction of POL Depot and Laying of 2 Nos MS/HSD Jetty Pipelines  of M/s Indian Oil Corporation Ltd At Andrott, UT of Lakshadweep
Alternative Site Examined: Not applicable as the project or activity is site specific
Project Description: The project is meant for Indian Oil Corporation Limited . It is proposed to construct 3 nos. of above ground horizontal (AGHT) tanks of capacity 70 KL each for HFHSD storage (C class) and 2 nos. of underground (UG) tanks of 50 KL capacity each for storing MS (A Class). The total safe capacity of the depot including HFHSD and MS will be 310 KL.;It is also proposed to construct 2 product pipelines to receive products from jetty to depot tanks from tanker.  MS product pipeline with 80mm dia and HF HSD with 150mm dia and approximately 600 m length from Depot to Jetty will be constructed. Total area of the Depot 2148.52 sqm.

Alternative Site Description: The site is found suitable for the proposed project.

Project Name: Development of Water Aerodrome at Kavaratti Island, Lakshadweep
Alternative Site Description: Site Selected based on feasibility of the water level depth for the proposed water aerodrome
